==English==

===Etymology===
From Punjabi [[ਗੁਰਮੁਖੀ]] (''Gurmukhī''), commonly translated as "from the Mouth of the Guru", since it was standardised by Guru Angad Dev in the 16th century.

===Proper noun===
{{en-proper noun}}

# An [[abugida]] [[script]], or writing system, designed for writing the [[Punjabi]] language. It has been adapted to write other languages, such as [[Braj Bhasha]], [[Hindi]], [[Sanskrit]] and [[Sindhi]].

